master.commit_message:
stress-sigbus: unconstify ptr8, clean up pedantic warnings:

stress-sigbus.c:215:35: warning: cast from 'const unsigned char *' to 'unsigned long *' drops const qualifier [-Wcast-qual]
                                uint64_t *ptr64 = (uint64_t *)(ptr8 + 1);
                                                              ^
stress-sigbus.c:216:35: warning: cast from 'const unsigned char *' to 'unsigned int *' drops const qualifier [-Wcast-qual]
                                uint32_t *ptr32 = (uint32_t *)(ptr8 + 1);
                                                              ^
stress-sigbus.c:217:35: warning: cast from 'const unsigned char *' to 'unsigned short *' drops const qualifier [-Wcast-qual]
                                uint16_t *ptr16 = (uint16_t *)(ptr8 + 1);

Signed-off-by: Colin Ian King <colin.i.king@gmail.com>

core-*: rename system_{read|write} to stress_system_{read|write}

standardize stress helper function naming

Signed-off-by: Colin Ian King <colin.i.king@gmail.com>

